# Install Splunk Entreprise on EC2. It runs very quickly
Step 0: Assuming that you re familiar with AWS platform and EC2 instance.
The sc
Step 1: Download
username: ThuHuongLE
pw: $plunkEntr3prise
Check disk space on ec2 : df -hT /dev/xvda1

Step 2: Create VM, log in with key pair
>>make new folder >> move key to the folder >> chmod 400 >> connect (ssh username@ip_add -i key.pem)
>> mkdir SSH >> mv filename.pem SSH >> chmod400 filename.pem >> ssh ec2-user@ip-name -i filename.pem

Step 3: Copy rpm to cloud server
scp -i /Users/trungngo/Downloads/SSH/Stockholm-t3micro-KPpem.pem splunk-7.2.4.2-fb30470262e3-linux-2.6-x86_64.rpm ec2-user@13.48.57.49:/tmp

Step 4: install rpm -i directory
sudo su
rpm -i /tmp/splunk-7.2.4.2-fb30470262e3-linux-2.6-x86_64.rpm 
to check 
ll /opt/splunk to see all dir (pwd)


Step 5: create admin credential
vim /opt/splunk/etc/system/local/user-seed.conf
write
[user_info]
USERNAME= admin
PASSWORD= $plunkEntr3prise
press SHIFT and type :w to save then :q to exist

Step 6: boot for production
ll /opt/splunk to see all folder, care for bin
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start --accept-license
to check ll /etc/systemd/system , to see Splunkd.service
systemctl status Splunkd , status is disable
systemctl start Splunkd
ll var/log/splunk/, to check a bunch of log file

Step 7 : access to public IP4:8000 port
